# COMMANDES
## Verif interface graphique

`ls /usr/bin/*session` pr uniquement notre session

## Verif le parefeu

`sudo ufw status`

`sudo service ufw status`

puis verif que cest bien active

## Verif le service ssh

`sudo service ssh status`

## Verif l'OS

`uname -v`

## Check user and group

`getent group sudo user42`

## Add user and check pssw

`sudo adduser <user>`

## Add group

`sudo addgroup evaluating`

## Check adding to group

`sudo adduser <user> <group>`

## Check hostname

`hostname`

## Check change hostname

`sudo nano /etc/hostname`
 
 `hostnamectl set-hostname <name>` pr changer egalement a laffichage le hostname
	`nano /etc/hostname` 

`sudo /etc/hosts`

## Check partitions

`lsblk`

## Check sudo

`which -v`

## Check and add sudo group

`sudo adduser <user> sudo`

`getent group sudo`

## Check sudo rules

`nano /ect/sudoers.d/sudo_config`

## Check sudo logs

`cd /var/log/sudo`

`ls`

`cat sudo_config`
pour montrer que le chemin d'acces existe et quil contient un fichier

## Check UFW advanced

`dpkg -s ufw` pr veri fqu ecest bien instqlle

`sudo servic ufw status`

## Check ufw active rules

`sudo ufw status numbered`

## Check rule creation

`sudo ufw allow <port>` add

`sudo ufw delete <num_rule>` del 

## Check SSh advanced

`which ssh`

`sudo service ssh status`

## Check SSH usage

`ssh <user>@localhost -p 4142`

## Check crontab of script

`sudo crontab -u root -e`






